1- Download cassandra-server from http://cassandra.apache.org/download/
2- $ tar -zxvf apache-cassandra-$VERSION.tar.gz
3- $ cd apache-cassandra-$VERSION
4- Creation of logs:
   $ sudo mkdir -p /var/log/cassandra
   $ sudo chown -R `whoami` /var/log/cassandra
   $ sudo mkdir -p /var/lib/cassandra
   $ sudo chown -R `whoami` /var/lib/cassandra

5- Add CASSANDRA_HOME to PATH
6- start server with cassandra -f
7- start cql with cqlsh with server up

NOTES: if at any point cqlsh refuses with a connection shutdown on port 9160 -> rm -Rf ~/.cassandra
